This paper discusses the interpretability of machine learning models, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the motivations for interpretability, which relates to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the feasibility and desirability of different notions of interpretability, which relates to the field of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the properties and techniques that confer interpretability, which relates to the field of cybernetics (cs.CY).
